messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path:
  /printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID}

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The method in ManagerController is annotated with:
  @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID}", method = RequestMethod.DELETE)
  which maps exactly the path /printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID} and only the HTTP DELETE method.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping that would add a prefix to the path, so the full path is exactly as declared.
- Only the DELETE method is explicitly declared in the code for this endpoint; per the instruction to base answers on the code (not framework runtime behavior), no other HTTP methods are considered acceptable even if the framework might implicitly handle OPTIONS or HEAD.
